statement:
\emph{Multiple Choice Question: Exactly ONE of the answers provided is
correct. There is no partial credit in this questions.}

Consider the differential equation

\begin{align*}\frac{dy}{dt} = 1-4y^2\end{align*} and initial condition $y(0) = 0.$ After a
long time (when $y$ no longer changes), the value of $y$ is

\begin{description}
\itemsep1pt\parskip0pt\parsep0pt
\item[]
\emph{i.} $y = 0$
\end{description}

\begin{description}
\itemsep1pt\parskip0pt\parsep0pt
\item[]
\emph{ii.} $y = 1$
\end{description}

\begin{description}
\itemsep1pt\parskip0pt\parsep0pt
\item[]
\emph{iii.} $y = 1/4$
\end{description}

\begin{description}
\itemsep1pt\parskip0pt\parsep0pt
\item[]
\emph{iv.} $y = 4$
\end{description}

\begin{description}
\itemsep1pt\parskip0pt\parsep0pt
\item[]
\emph{v.} $y = 1/2$
\end{description}
